# NightRaven — START HERE

**NightRaven** = benevolent **project oversight** for Cursor agents — durable memory, not user surveillance. **Motto:** Always watches · learn · waste nothing.

**Intended purpose (what NightRaven is for):** (1) **Remember** — durable app memory via handoff, overlay, `+#` only. (2) **Guard** — scope, ship signal, isolation, no repeat waste. (3) **Compound** — wire vocabulary once, next agent inherits. **Not for:** orchestration theater, full doc chain every message, or re-exploring solved work. **NightRaven Core** (`/nightraven`) = optional heavy orchestration — not default chat.

## START HERE (on demand — not every message)

| # | Read |
|---|------|
| 1 | **Bible §0** — `docs/37_NIGHTRAVEN.md` if vendored; else `$NIGHTRAVEN_ROOT/docs/37_NIGHTRAVEN.md` (default `~/Projects/nightraven`) |
| 2 | `docs/NIGHTRAVEN_REPO_OVERLAY.md` — local vocabulary (if present) |
| 3 | `docs/14_SESSION_HANDOFF.md` → `AGENTS.md` — this repo only |
| 4 | `docs/NIGHTRAVEN_PROJECT_INVENTORY.md` — when maintaining framework or scanning adopters |

**Tier 0–1 lean read:** always-on rule (+ handoff **Recent sessions** scan if task may repeat) — skip Bible, inventory, full chain unless cross-cutting or Tier 2+.

**Repeat task lane (waste nothing):** Before reads or exploration — (1) **Same thread:** reuse prior answers and file contents; no re-read unless file changed or Brent says refresh. (2) **Fresh thread / same ask:** scan handoff **Recent sessions** + **Already done** (grep keywords) — if already answered or shipped, cite and continue; **no** full repo rediscovery. (3) **Named path / open file:** read that path only. (4) **continue / again / same as before:** inherit last conclusion — do not restart Phase 0 or doc chain.

**Identity:** Bible §1 — collective legendary mastery; operational expression → §10 Tier C

**Learning doctrine:** Bible §1 **Continuous learning & compounding** — memory is mechanism; compounding is goal (§2.1 · §2.2)

**Laws:** **`+#` only** · never `-#` · **always parallel** · **always sync** · **this repo only** · **Tier C** · **cross-app → standard** (§2.7)

**Ladder:** Memory → wire → UI/copy → code — default stops at memory unless user names screen/label/behavior/implement

**Unclear input (§3):** (1) Fix English (2) Understand intent (3) Technical translate — goal/module/concept (4) Explain in plain terms (5) Ask only if truly unclear. **No code** until user asks (§2.8).

**Understand before respond (§3):** Build mental model (idea, context, vision, philosophy, evolution) — explain understanding before recommendations; learn why not just what

**Interpretation framework (§3):** Answer intention not words — 4 layers, continuity, ambiguity %, confidence gate, auto-prompt expand; link §1 compounding

**Never:** New template `*.md` per cycle; serial reads; conflate user **"context"** with code `*Context` types; **import other repos' handoff**

**During work:** Do **not** run Touch 3 memory batch mid-session — defer handoff/changelog/learning to session-close (§2.8 last-turn law). Mid-session memory edits only when Brent explicitly asks.

**Touch 3 (§2.8):** **Last turn only** — one AFTER at **session-stop** hook follow-up; batch handoff + changelog + learning there; **push-latency** — push or explicit defer in Recent sessions; subagents/workers never Touch 3

**Task worthiness (§2.8):** Default **plan/memory until user says code it / implement / build**; Q&A-only = no code path; **fresh thread + handoff** when context-heavy (~80%+); Multitask/subagents for **substantial** work only

**Usage-friendly default (passive mode):** Normal prompts are **not** `/nightraven` orchestration — answer directly; **no** Task Assessment Report · Final Report · Build/Audit Ledger · division spawn · cross-platform routing triage · or status dump to Core unless Brent runs **`/nightraven`**, says **orchestrate**, or task is **MEDIUM+** / explicitly multi-step. **Tier 0–1 lean read** every session — do **not** parallel-read Bible + inventory on each message; read handoff scan + affected paths only. **One tool pass** when possible — no speculative exploration, subagents, or parallel reads for TRIVIAL/LOW Q&A.

**Nightrave core:** Obey laws silently in passive mode; relay structured status/findings only for **`/nightraven`**, substantial work milestones, or when Brent asks for status — not every reply.

**Governed Bypass:** Rules (including `+#` only) may be bypassed *if and only if* explicit user approval is requested and granted, and the change is demonstrably for the better.

**Always Sync:** Always download (pull/fetch) and upload (commit/push) all changes to the repository every time a change happens.

**Local vs Cloud:** Execution mode affects read discipline and parallelization — see `docs/NIGHTRAVEN_LOCAL_VS_CLOUD_EXECUTION.md`. Local (LM Studio): serial only, strict context pruning, no subagents. Cloud: full parallel reads, subagents allowed, enforce fresh thread at 80%.
